 Mini project  : STUDENT COURSE ENROLLMENT SYSTEM (JAVA – OOPS)  
1. Program Title :  
Student Course Enrollment System using Java (Core Logic + Data Structure)  
2. Problem Statement :  
To develop the core logic and data structure backbone for managing student 
course enrollment using Java OOP concepts.  
3. Objective :  
• To implement OOP concepts  
• To use ArrayList for data storage  
• To manage student-course relationships  
4. Tools Used :  
• Java (JDK)  
• VS Code / Command Prompt  
5. Description :  
This program implements the core logic of a Student Course Enrollment  
System using Java. It uses classes like Student and Course, and an 
EnrollmentSystem class to manage them. ArrayList is used as the data structure to 
store students and courses. The program allows adding, searching, and enrolling 
students into courses.  
  
6. Algorithm :  
1. Start   
2. Create Course class   
3. Create Student class with ArrayList   
4. Create EnrollmentSystem class   
5. Add students and courses   
6. Search using ID   
7. Enroll student   
8. Display courses   
9. Stop   
  
7. Program (Java Code) :  
import java.util.ArrayList;  
  
class Course {  
    int id;  
    String name;  
  
    Course(int id, String name) {  
        this.id = id;  
        this.name = name;  
    }  
}  
  
class Student {  
    int id;  
    String name;  
    ArrayList<Course> courses = new ArrayList<>();  
  
    Student(int id, String name) {  
        this.id = id;  
        this.name = name;  
    }  
  
    void enroll(Course c) {  
        courses.add(c);  
    }  
  
    void display() {         for (Course c : 
courses) {             
System.out.println(c.name);  
        }  
    }  
}  
  
class EnrollmentSystem {  
    ArrayList<Student> students = new ArrayList<>();  
    ArrayList<Course> courses = new ArrayList<>();  
  
    void addStudent(Student s) {  
        students.add(s);  
    }  
  
    void addCourse(Course c) {  
        courses.add(c);  
    }  
  
    Student findStudent(int id) {         
for (Student s : students) {             
if (s.id == id)  
                return s;  
        }  
        return null;  
    }  
  
    Course findCourse(int id) {  
        for (Course c : courses) {             
if (c.id == id)  
                return c;  
        }  
        return null;  
    }  
  
    void enrollStudent(int sid, int cid) {         
Student s = findStudent(sid);         
Course c = findCourse(cid);         if (s != 
null && c != null) {             s.enroll(c);  
        }  
    }  
}  
  
public class Main {  
    public static void main(String[] args) {  
  
        EnrollmentSystem sys = new EnrollmentSystem();  
  
        Student s = new Student(1, "Aswini");  
        Course c = new Course(101, "Java");  
  
        sys.addStudent(s);  
sys.addCourse(c);  
sys.enrollStudent(1, 101);  
s.display();  
} 
}   
9. Result :  
Thus the Java program for Student Course Enrollment System using core logic and 
data structure was executed successfully.  
10. Conclusion :  
This program demonstrates Java OOP concepts and uses ArrayList as the data 
structure to implement student-course enrollment efficiently.  
